  "original_title": "Sri Lanka immigration dept opens separate passport counter for job seekers",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka immigration dept opens separate passport counter for job seekers",
      "author": "Neshella Perera",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s Department of Immigration and Emigration in collaboration with the Bureau of Foreign Employment have opened a separate counter at the Immigration Department for the issue of urgent passports for those seeking employment overseas.",
        "An official from the Department of Immigration told EconomyNext on Wednesday August 24 that the number of passports issued for June was 120,000, for July 101,777 and as of Wednesday, 77,557 passports had been issued for August.",
        "The new counter has been opened as an urgent counter and passports are issued under one-day service, with the price being 15,000 rupees for passport completion within the day. Applicants who have completed their initial process and have obtained a letter pertaining to their employment from the Sri Lanka Bureau of Foreign Employment (SLBFE) can obtain their passports soon by providing the document at the newly opened counter, the official said.",
        "A growing number of Sri Lankans are looking for jobs overseas due to the country\u2019s economic meltdown which has accelerated expenditure way beyond income earned. Inflation for July rose to 66.7 percent.",
        "Minister of Foreign Employment Manusha Nanayakkara had advised the opening of the counter following discussions with SLBFE officials of and the Immigration and Emigration Department last week, the official said. (Colombo/Aug24/2022)"
      ],
